gate: OPEN
sprint: S05
track: A
task: A1
title: "fix(delivery): bound UPS per-attempt timeout (#259 phase 2)"
repos: [crop-parts-services]
priority: high
refs:
  - CROP-parts-services#259
  - S02 hot-path map: ups-address.ts:30, fetchWithRetry
requires: [BUN_HONO_CLOUDRUN]

description: |
  The UPS XAV provider uses fetchWithRetry with no per-attempt timeout ceiling.
  A slow UPS response can hold the delivery Cloud Run instance for up to 35s
  (the FE client timeout at lib/delivery-api/client.ts:214).
  Fix: add AbortSignal.timeout(8s) per attempt inside the UPS provider.
  8s leaves room for 2 retries within the 35s FE ceiling.

ground_truth:
  file: CROP-parts-services/services/delivery/src/providers/ups/ups-address.ts
  line: 30   # fetchWithRetry call — no AbortSignal passed
  fe_timeout: 35s (lib/delivery-api/client.ts:214)
  target_per_attempt: 8s

scope:
  in:
    - ups-address.ts — add AbortSignal.timeout(8_000) per attempt
    - fetchWithRetry helper — accept and forward signal param
    - Unit test: mock fetch hangs → expect abort within ceiling
  out:
    - FE client timeout (leave at 35s)
    - OAuth fetch (covered in A2)

acceptance:
  - Per-attempt UPS XAV call aborts at ≤ 8s
  - AbortError surfaces as 504/timeout to caller — not swallowed
  - Unit test: hang mock → abort confirmed

dep: none
output: ups-address.ts + fetchWithRetry patched + unit test
